        <section>
            <h2>Early Life</h2>
            <p>Michael Jackson was born in 1958 in Gary, Indiana. He showed an early interest in music and began performing
                at a young age, influenced by his family's musical background. Growing up in a strict household, his
                father, Joe Jackson, pushed him and his siblings to perform. By age 5, Michael was already singing and
                performing, and by 6, he became the lead singer of the Jackson 5, the group formed with his brothers.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="career">
            <h2>Jackson 5</h2>
            <p>Michael Jackson joined the <strong>Jackson 5</strong> in 1964, alongside his brothers. As the lead singer, he
                gained fame for his impressive voice and stage presence. The group signed with Motown Records in 1968,
                releasing hits like:</p>

            <!-- Unordered List for Songs -->
            <ul>
                <li>"I Want You Back"</li>
                <li>"ABC"</li>
                <li>"I'll Be There"</li>
                <li>"Dancing Machine"</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Their success made them one of the most popular acts of the 1970s. Michael's talent and charisma began to
                shine, setting the stage for his future solo career.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Top Albums</h2>
            <!-- Ordered List for Albums -->
            <ol>
                <li>Off the Wall (1979)</li>
                <li>Thriller (1982)</li>
                <li>Bad (1987)</li>
                <li>Dangerous (1991)</li>
                <li>HIStory: Past, Present and Future, Book I (1995)</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Major Achievements</h2>
            <!-- Unordered List for Achievements -->
            <ul>
                <li>Most awarded artist in history</li>
                <li>First artist to have a #1 hit in four different decades</li>
                <li>Thriller remains the best-selling album of all time</li>
                <li>Inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame twice</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

